# VPS crontab — BASE (system / vault / integration / generic agent jobs).
# This is NOT the whole crontab: per-agent jobs live in ~/vault/agents/<name>/crontab.
# Install with: ~/code/dotfiles/build-crontab.sh   (merges base + all agent fragments)
# Do NOT run `crontab ~/code/dotfiles/crontab.vps` directly — it would drop every
# agent's cron. NEVER use `crontab -e`. Edit this file or an agent fragment, commit,
# then re-run build-crontab.sh. See the rule in ~/vault/CLAUDE.md.
#
# Previous drift incident (2026-04-06 → 2026-04-08): the live crontab had extra
# entries not in this file. The dotfile was re-installed around the kernel-upgrade
# reboot and clobbered overnight, leann rebuild, LinkedIn sync script name, and
# inbox collection cadence. Fixed 2026-04-08.

# bash, NOT the /bin/sh default: ~/.secret_env uses process substitution
# (`source <(op inject ...)`), which dash cannot parse — under sh every
# `. ~/.secret_env && ...` job dies silently at the source line. This killed
# LinkedIn sync + Mapcamp monitor from 2026-06-04 (when .secret_env went
# self-generating) until caught 2026-06-11 via the missed Kit ICP sweep.
SHELL=/bin/bash

# ---- Vault & sync ----

# Rotate agent stream logs (keep last 1MB to preserve tail context)
0 0 * * * truncate -s 1048576 /tmp/worker-1-stream.jsonl 2>/dev/null

# Prune daily-rotated worker usage logs older than 30 days (per-turn token+cost data)
5 0 * * * find /tmp -maxdepth 1 -name 'worker-*-usage-*.jsonl' -mtime +30 -delete 2>/dev/null

# Prune raw pi request payloads older than 14 days (set by run-worker.sh via PI_LOG_REQUESTS)
6 0 * * * find /tmp/pi-requests -mindepth 1 -mtime +14 -delete 2>/dev/null

# Vault git backup (5 min)
*/5 * * * * ~/bin/vault-sync.sh >> ~/bin/vault-sync.log 2>&1

# Google Drive transcript sync
*/20 * * * * ~/bin/sync-drive-transcripts.sh

# ---- Inbox collection ----
# Central heartbeat RETIRED 2026-06-06: reminders → agent reminder reflexes,
# pre-meeting briefings → Carly/Bobby morning calendar callout, project overdue →
# Penelope's board audit. See agents/Spec - Retire Central Heartbeat.md.
# Em's own collect + digest cron moved to agents/em/crontab 2026-06-06 (self-contained).

# NOTE: per-agent scheduled jobs (Penelope, Bella, …) now live in
# ~/vault/agents/<name>/crontab and are merged in by build-crontab.sh.

# ---- Daily batch work ----

# Overnight skill RETIRED 2026-06-06 — its duties moved to agents: daily-note shell → Penelope,
# service health → Bella, newsletter → Maggie, periodic reviews → Miriam, blog/webinar → Maggie
# reminders, pay-salary → Charles reminder. Content/YNAB/Xero already covered by Maggie/Charles.
# BAU projects retired with it. See projects/Multi-Agent Transition…/ and agents/RUNTIME-DESIGN.md.

# PostHog anomaly scan RETIRED 2026-06-06 — the broad all-project/Airskills daily scan
# was too general for the new agent split. Maggie now owns a chrismdp.com/blog/content
# PostHog read in agents/maggie/crontab; Bobby owns RightMessage-led commercial
# segmentation and may use PostHog only as supporting funnel evidence.
# 0 6 * * * /home/cp/.claude/skills/posthog-scan/scripts/run.sh

# Process yesterday's CC sessions at 06:30 UTC — activity summary + wiki ingest (was Step 1 of /overnight)
30 6 * * * /home/cp/.claude/skills/process-sessions/scripts/run.sh

# Bluesky feed curator MOVED to ~/vault/agents/maggie/crontab (Maggie owns it now,
# 2026-06-05) — her reflex dispatches her to run the /bluesky skill; her reply is the
# surface (own bot), no more send.sh → kim. The old run.sh is retired.


# Financial reconciliation cron MOVED to ~/vault/agents/charles/crontab (Charles owns
# it now — the engine runs there, then hands its result into Charles's chat to surface).

# Nightly dream MOVED to ~/vault/agents/richard/crontab (Richard owns reading-shaped
# wiki synthesis and routes concrete follow-ups to the relevant domain agent).

# Telegram project-map cleanup
0 4 * * * /home/cp/.claude/skills/telegram/scripts/project-map.sh clean >> /tmp/telegram-webhook.log 2>&1

# LEANN vault index rebuild — REMOVED 2026-06-04. leann was unreliable to rebuild
# (300K-token batch overflow, ~12GB OOM on this box) and repeated re-embeds cost
# real money. Semantic search is on hold until Trove replaces it; `leann` in PATH
# is now a deprecation shim pointing at grep. Do not re-add without a working,
# cost-bounded indexer.

# Claude Code session export (every 30 min — writes today's sessions to vault for cross-machine aggregation)
*/30 * * * * python3 ~/.claude/skills/process-sessions/export_claude_sessions.py --today >/dev/null 2>&1

# ---- Integrations ----

# Kit ICP sweep — enrol ICP subscribers into "Ask how doing" (~/code/kit-webhooks)
# KIT_API_KEY is deliberately NOT in .secret_env (agents must not inherit it) — op read it here.
4 8 * * 1-5 . ~/.secret_env && export KIT_API_KEY="$(op read 'op://AI Agent/Kit API/v4 key')" && python3 ~/code/kit-webhooks/icp_sweep.py >> /tmp/kit-icp-sweep.log 2>&1

# Mapcamp monitor
0 9 * * * . ~/.secret_env && python3 /home/cp/scripts/monitor-mapcamp.py >> /tmp/monitor-mapcamp.log 2>&1

# Home Assistant camera snapshots -> Google Drive (noon UK time)
0 11,12 * * * /home/cp/scripts/ha-snapshots.sh

# Calendar-aware HA state (every 15 min): pushes binary_sensor.chris_on_holiday
# (from chris.p@rsons.org OOO events — used by heater_morning_up to skip on holidays),
# sensor.outdoor_temperature (from weather entity, for long-term stats),
# and sensor.office_temperature_c (Fahrenheit source converted to Celsius).
*/15 * * * * /home/cp/.claude/skills/home/scripts/ha-calendar-status.py >> /tmp/ha-calendar-status.log 2>&1

# Litter tray check (15:00 UK time; sleeps until sunset+15, capped at 21:00, snapshots + Gemini verdict)
# DISABLED 2026-05-23 (Chris asked to stop — Poppins doing it now): 0 14,15 * * * /home/cp/.claude/skills/home/scripts/litter-tray-check.sh

# DISABLED 2026-05-26 (Chris asked to stop — Poppins doing it now): 0 8 * * 2 . ~/.secret_env && python3 ~/vault/scripts/everyman-winchester-check.py >> /tmp/everyman-check.log 2>&1

